# Spec Documents

## Constitution (specs/constitution/)
These files are invariants. Never violate them. If a task conflicts with the constitution, STOP and flag it.

- `mission.md` — why this product exists and for whom.
- `tech-stack.md` — approved libraries and frameworks. Do not introduce new dependencies without updating this file.
- `roadmap.md` — phases and feature sequencing. Do not build out-of-sequence.
- `non-functionals.md` — security, auth, validation, error-handling, performance, scalability, and data-quality requirements.

## Feature Specs (specs/features/<feature>/)
Each feature has three documents:

- `plan.md` — what to build, why, and how it fits the roadmap.
- `requirements.md` — numbered requirements (R1, R2...) each with a clear acceptance scenario.
- `validation.md` — checklist of acceptance scenarios, marked TODO → IN_PROGRESS → PASSED.

## Writing a new feature spec
Use the template at `specs/features/_template/`. Copy it, rename, fill in requirements before touching any code.
